article.headline: Lafayette 70, Towson 63
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- Andrew Brown scored 20 points and Lafayette defeated Towson 70-63 on Sunday. Michael Gruner added 11 points for Lafayette (3-8), which rallied from an 11-point first-half deficit. Junior Hairston had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Jarrel Smith added 15 points and 11 boards, and Josh Thornton shot 5-for-11 from 3-point range and finished with 17 points for Towson (5-7). Lafayette's substitutes outscored their Towson counterparts 21-3. Towson outscored Lafayette 15-4 on second-change points and 6-4 on the fast break.
